There is no need to create a huge, bulky technological infrastructure that will inevitably expand to store records of the daily movements of individual citizens.
Nevada is one of only a handful of states where a difficult search for inexpensive technology is underway that would allow state authorities to count the miles driven by a car, but without information about the location and time.
