Energy engineers of Dnepropetrovsk started a unique program of rescue...
In the olden days, to lead to the yard of the donkeys, the peasants mounted a wheel from the cart on a high pillar, and the heavy nest was well held on it.
Such special supports have not been put for a long time, so the Aists loved columns of power lines - interwoven branches rely on wires, thanks to which a real house stands reliably.
Grandmother Anja, near whose house a real family has lived in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district for twenty years, began to notice how the nest settles, despite all the efforts of its inhabitants.
Birds lay new branches on top, and the lower layer has already passed between the wires, here it will collapse.
Of course, sadly, the seven donkeys, who each year nested at the yard, brought out and fed for the summer three or four chicks, but even without the light do not want to stay.
As soon as the birds flew to the warm edges, Grandmother Anja called the Tsarichansky power plant, which owns the support.
I didn’t expect them to react so quickly.
When our specialists arrived in Ivanovka, they were surprised that the nest is still standing at all, - said the technical director of the DTEK "Dneprooblanergo" Sergey Berezovsky.
On the wires, which were, in fact, already inside the socket, weighing 150-200 kilograms, began corrosion.
At any moment, the birds could be killed by an electric shock.
The locals also risked being left without light due to damage to the wires.
Therefore, the liners began the operation to save the nest, and not for the first time in our practice.
Scientists-ornithologists from the Dnepropetrovsk National University helped to develop a scheme for the transfer of the nest.
They also conducted trainings for employees of district networks.
The famous Dnepropetrovsk ornithologist Alexander Ponomarenko consulted energy scientists at all stages of the reconstruction of the nests.
To begin with, it was calculated that there are more than 50 real "apartments" in the area in a state of emergency.
For their reconstruction were welded special metal platforms, resembling a funnel.
The base was woven with ivory branches, and then moved an old nest there.
According to experts, it is enough to lay old branches as a basis for the birds to recognize the nest and return to it.
After that, the aristocrats will build their own homes.
A month ago, the first nest was reconstructed in the village of Peschanka of Novomoskovsky district.
Next to the electric pole was placed a new concrete pillar and placed on it a platform with an old, already enclosed nest.
The whole operation cost the energy workers nine thousand hryvnias.
And in the days the same new settlement took place in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district in the yard of grandmother Ani.
Here the platform was fixed in the previous place, only raised above the wires.
Ornithologists are sure that cautious, conservative birds will not even notice in the spring that their "apartment" was subject to capital repair.
By the end of the year, the same reconstruction awaits four more nests in Pokrovsky and Tsarichansky districts of Dnepropetrovsk.
By the way, while some save rare birds, others relentlessly kill them.
In the days, the whole area was covered with sad news - in the village of Ust-Kamenka Apostolovsky district, on the day of the discovery of the hunt for fazans, cockroaches for entertainment shot a swan family living on a local pond.
Noble birds were not afraid of humans at all - the locals fed them and did not hurt them.
When the villagers heard the shots, they ran to the pond, and the four beautiful swamps were already lying dead on the water.
Now the employees of the Apostolic District Department of the police find out who shot at the birds included in the Red Book.
"Russian March" is becoming more popular
On November 4, on the Day of People's Unity, a concerted "Russian March" will take place in Moscow.
