I have reached the point of political desperation.
The obstructionism of the Republicans cannot explain the permission to interrogate foreign leaders or to strike unmanned children in other countries.
It cannot explain the collection of data on the privacy of Americans by the National Security Agency or the prosecution of detainees revealing the government’s wrongful actions.
He cannot explain the murder of American citizen Anwar al-Awlaki without trial and investigation or non-compliance with the limits of state funding and spending during presidential campaigns.
He cannot justify the findings of the report, which states that the White House’s efforts to silence the media are “the most aggressive ... since the Nixon administration.”
